<p1>Opening Stock, also called Beginning Inventory, refers to the quantity held by a company at the beginning of the accounting period. Similarly, it is the ending stock of the preceding year and is carried forward to the next year.</p1><br>
<p2>Opening Stock, also called Beginning Inventory, refers to the quantity held by a company at the beginning of the accounting period. Similarly, it is the ending stock of the preceding year and is carried forward to the next year.</p2>
